revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Light_MinNeighbor}} {{Special|233|tag|Lighting|MinNeighbor}} * ''tag'': Tag of affected sector
Sets the light level of a sector to match the lowest light level found in one of its neighboring sectors.
==Examples== {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Light_MinNeighbor: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Doom}} 104:W1 Light To Lowest Adjacent Level || Light_MinNeighbor (tag) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Boom}} 157:WR Light To Lowest Adjacent Level || Light_MinNeighbor (tag) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 173:S1 Light To Lowest Adjacent Level || Light_MinNeighbor (tag) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 194:SR Light To Lowest Adjacent Level || Light_MinNeighbor (tag) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
